Under the new crown pneumonia epidemic, Hubei, a serious epidemic area, is facing a serious shortage of medical and living materials. Masks, protective clothing, goggles, fresh fruits and vegetables all need outside support, most businesses are helping to tide over the stricken areas. However, in the current critical situation, how to quickly mobilize materials and send them to the front line into use has become the key.

E-commerce platform by virtue of its own original supply chain and platform advantages, in response to the needs of the epidemic area to take direct point-to-point assistance, the first time to give material support. In addition, road closures and transportation disruptions have caused problems in the circulation of agricultural products, and the platform has tried to build procurement and purchase channels and give subsidies to farmers who have worked hard for a year without suffering losses in the sale of agricultural products, to feed the people of the city.

Staff at the Sixth People's Hospital in Wuhan, Hubei Province, carry vegetables and fruits donated by Pinduoduo on February 2.

A driver and a truck full of fruits and vegetables

At 6 p.m. on New Year's Eve, a loud noise came from behind the car, the second time Li Chao had a flat tire. At that time, he was only a few dozen kilometers away from Peking Union Medical College Hospital in Jingmen, Hubei. The car was loaded with materials donated by Pinduoduo to the hospital. Since the outbreak of the new pneumonia, the hospital has been extremely short of vegetables and fruits, his load was sent to the emergency room.

Li Chao, a truck driver in Xiangyang, Hubei Province, has been driving to the countryside every day since the outbreak to deliver feed to farms. Around 10:00 a.m. on the 10th day of the Lunar New Year, he received a phone call, hoping to coordinate a car and a driver, "Hurry up with some fresh vegetables and fruits to Peking Union Hospital in Jingmen, a designated hospital for COVID-19 pneumonia patients. "

At the time, his wife was silent, but Li Chao could tell she didn't want him to get off the train. The 39-year-old Li Chao, who has 70-year-old parents and a teenage son, "would not be good if he came back with the virus and passed it on to the elderly and children. ". After a second or two of hesitation, Li Chao agreed and decided to deliver the fruits and vegetables himself.

Li Chao went to the yard to pick up some fresh fruits and vegetables, which Doddo had donated to Peking Union Hospital. On his way out of the city, Li Chao went directly to Peking Union Medical College Hospital before twelve o'clock. Although I have been a truck driver for more than 10 years, I have never been to Jingshan County. It is a strange journey. But soon after Xiangyang, the highway was closed and he had to go around the national highway and had a flat and a change of tire on the right rear.

However, as we turned onto the highway and got closer and closer to our destination, the other side of the car had a flat tire with a loud bang. At this time, Li Chao completely panic: "I heard that the hospital fresh vegetables nervous, spell Doddo finally collected these fruits and vegetables, slow, too sorry everyone. " However, fortunately, the hospital to contact the master to solve this obstacle, shortly after 8 p.m. , Li Chao and the truck full of fresh produce finally arrived at their destination.

"The hospital organized off-duty doctors and nurses to help unload the cargo. I saw them for a moment and tears came down. They were busy treating patients during the day and helping me unload the cargo at night. I was really moved. "

Fu Zheng, head of the Pinduoduo anti-epidemic Working Group, said, "health care workers and patients are in danger, and fresh fruits and vegetables are necessary to ensure their nutrition to fight the epidemic. But the things that are usually especially simple are very difficult to do at this time. The main reason is that it is difficult to raise materials and transport them. It is drivers like Li Chao who enable us to get these materials to the people who need them most, " Fu said, after the outbreak, pinduoduo emergency procurement of more than 100 tons of fresh fruits and vegetables, through logistics partners, directly sent to 16 hospitals in seven cities in Hubei.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
February 2, Hubei Xiangyang Bamboo Leaf Hill market, workers are to fight Doddo from all over the collection of agricultural products transported to the "epidemic" front.

Make a phone call, get a bunch of masks

"Do you have surgical masks? Even dozens of them. " On January 31, Paul Dirac, a member of Pinduoduo's "anti-epidemic working group, " received the call from Huanggang, Hubei Province.

The caller was Wang Bin, from the Xinguan pneumonia control headquarters in Huanggang, Hubei Province. Throughout the Spring Festival period, Wang Bin Every day in the search for medical protection materials. At the time, the focus of national attention was Wuhan, but when the city was closed and one hundred thousand people returned to Huanggang, medical supplies were desperately scarce and how could they fight without equipment?

"The first thing I do when I open my eyes every day is how to get medical masks and protective clothing, " Wang said. "We don't have much in stock. We can't open the door without this hospital. ". At the time, Huanggang's medical staff had to go nine hours without food or water to save their suits, which were scrapped when they went to the toilet.

Less than a day after Wang turned to Doddo for help, on the evening of January 31, pinduoduo shipped the first batch of more than 60,000 masks and 20,000 medical gloves to Huanggang. The shipment arrived in Huanggang and was distributed to frontline staff at designated hospitals such as the Dabie Mountains Regional Medical Center in downtown Huanggang, under the Unified Command of the headquarters.

In fact, Huanggang is not the only country in need. After the outbreak, Doddo received Wuhan, Huanggang, Tianmen, Xiangyang, Jingmen, Xiaogan, Yichang, and other seven cities in Hubei Province urgently in need of supplies for help. Since then, Pinduoduo has donated 1 million surgical masks, 200,000 pairs of gloves and 30 tons of German disinfectant to 16 hospitals in seven cities of Hubei Province. So far, Pinduoduo has responded to 62 requests for help from local organizations and institutions.

Paul Dirac said: "These materials are all bought by Doddo, through logistics partners, directly to the target of assistance. ". This point-to-point approach, without third-party contributions, is more efficient in its current state and allows for quicker response to the needs of the units seeking assistance."

It is understood that the general shortage of medical supplies in the country, the financing of supplies is only the first difficulty. Paul Dirac said the situation in the affected areas was urgent, complex and difficult. "In the early days of the rescue, the main difficulty was the shortage of materials, but now the logistics is getting more and more difficult. Many places are closed, and the front lines have to be qualified transport companies to enter, " he said. Despite the difficulties, with the support of logistics partners, Doddo did his best to get every surgical mask he could find into the hands of those who needed it most.

DODDO's donations were not limited to medical supplies in the fight against the disease. The reporter from Hsinking news learned that Pin Doddo has also jointly set up a 100 million yuan "virus infectious disease prevention and Control Fund" with Zhejiang University. This donation will be used exclusively to support the prevention and treatment of virus infection and respiratory infectious disease, in particular, the support of the new pneumonia epidemic protection and scientific research.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
On February 3, six tonnes of fruit and vegetables donated by Pinduoduo were shipped to the Laohekou CDC in Xiangyang, Hubei Province.

A farmer sold his two tons of onions

Wang Dong (not his real name) , a farmer in Jianshui County, Honghe Hani and Yi Autonomous Prefecture, plans to sell two tons of purple onions before the Spring Festival so he can plant rice. But he did not think that thousands of miles away in Hubei new crown pneumonia epidemic can affect his plateau farmers'livelihood. According to statistics, affected by the new crown pneumonia epidemic, Jianshui County 100 tons of onion unsalable, farmers will lose 2 million yuan.

On one side are farmers like Wang Dong, who can not sell their hard-planted onions. On the other side, urban residents are struggling to buy vegetables because of damaged sales of agricultural products, road closures and logistical difficulties. So, in Jianshui onion unsalable farmers get anxious information, Doddo will Jianshui onion into the "anti-epidemic agricultural goods" subsidy support program.

"In many agricultural areas, 'one hand needs production, the other hand needs epidemic prevention, ' but due to blocked sales, many farmers are discouraged and production has been greatly affected, " Paul Dirac said, doddo has been contacted by agricultural experts and scholars in the hope that they can work together to solve the problem of agricultural production and marketing in special periods, so as to minimize the impact of the epidemic on agricultural production.

In order to guarantee the production and marketing of agricultural products in the special period, Pinduoduo has launched a series of small and medium-sized agricultural products special activities since February 3.

"during this period, we will mainly do three things. First, we will work with the new farmers of the platform to make a list of commodities, comb the stock and quality of agricultural products in agricultural production areas, especially in poor areas, so as to 'push forward' those agricultural products that need to be sold. Second, we will ask local governments and relevant departments to coordinate to open up green channels for such agricultural products. Third, we will co-ordinate logistics resources such as Shunfeng and China Post to ensure that fresh agricultural products can reach consumers directly. "

On February 10, Pin Doddo officially launched the "anti-epidemic agricultural products" zone, which now covers nearly 400 agricultural production areas across the country, including more than 230 national-level poor counties and nearly 280,000 commodities. For the zone, Pinduoduo set up 500 million yuan of special commodity subsidies, at the same time, each agricultural products express will also enjoy 2 yuan of special logistics subsidies.

"We will do our best to help every farmer in this special period to minimize their losses, benefiting from the rise of Pinduoduo in Chinese agriculture, " Paul Dirac said.

By Li Kang, Hsinking Daily News
